    • resetPassword

      public void resetPassword​(java.lang.String username, java.lang.String oldPassword, java.lang.String newPassword) throws AuthenticationException, PersistenceException
      Resets a password from an old password. To reset an unknown password use emailResetPassword
      Parameters:
      username - The username that needs their password reset
      oldPassword - The old password for the user
      newPassword - The new password for the user
      Throws:
      AuthenticationException - If the provided current password is incorrect.
      PersistenceException - if there was an issue communicating with the database or (potentially?) the user does not exist.
